com.moki.manage.api
Class MokiManage

java.lang.Object
  com.moki.manage.api.MokiManage

public class MokiManage
extends java.lang.Object

This is the managing class for the MokiManage SDK In the Example implementation below MokiManage is initialized with the app key, app id, an Android Context and we enable App Settings Management, App Environment Management, and Security Compliance. We also set a counter which counts open activities, pausing and resuming MokiManage in order to preserve battery life. This pattern is only available on Android API levels 14 and above and you can choose not to use it if you want MokiManage to function in an always on capacity. 

 
public class MokiManageApplication extends Application implements Application.ActivityLifecycleCallbacks {
        private static MokiManageApplication instance;
        private MokiManage mmanage;
        private int activeActivityCount = 0;

        private final boolean enableASM = true; 
        private final boolean enableAEM = true; 
        private final boolean enableCompliance = true; 
        private final String appKey = "_YOUR_APP_KEY_HERE_";
        private final String appID = "_YOUR_APP_ID_HERE_";
        @Override
        public void onCreate() {
                super.onCreate();
                Context context = this;
                mmanage = MokiManage.sharedInstance(appKey, appID, context, enableASM, enableAEM, enableCompliance);
                registerActivityLifecycleCallbacks(this);
        instance = this;
        }

        public static MokiManageApplication instance(){
                return instance;
        }

        public  MokiManage mokiManage(){
                return mmanage;
        }

        @Override
        public void onActivityStarted(Activity activity) {
                activeActivityCount++;
                if(activeActivityCount == 1){
                        mmanage.resume();
                }
        }

        @Override
        public void onActivityStopped(Activity activity) {      
                activeActivityCount--;
                if(activeActivityCount == 0){
                        mmanage.pause();
                }
        }

        @Override
        public void onActivityCreated(Activity activity, Bundle savedInstanceState) {
        }

        @Override
        public void onActivityDestroyed(Activity activity) {    
        }

        @Override
        public void onActivityPaused(Activity activity) {
        }

        @Override
        public void onActivityResumed(Activity activity) {
        }

        @Override
        public void onActivitySaveInstanceState(Activity activity, Bundle outState) {   
        }

}

sendAlerts

public void sendAlerts(java.lang.String... alertIds)
Send a list of alerts IDs to the server. MokiManage will only send alerts once every 15 minutes and otherwise queues a Unique Set of alerts for execution at the next 15 minute interval. 
  mokiMangage.sendAlerts("id from web","id from web");

Parameters:
alertIds - One or more alert ID's to be sent to the server

                      java.lang.String optionalMessage)
Send an alert to the server with an optional message. MokiManage will only send alerts once every 15 minutes and otherwise queues a Unique Set of alerts for execution at the next 15 minute interval. 
 mokiMangage.sendAlert("id from web","My custom message");

Parameters:
alertId - The alert ID to be sent
optionalMessage - The message to be sent
